<p>The challenge we have had is the command works as expected except we cannot cancel it. We can’t take over the command with the drive sticks or anything else until it is done. We have tried a number of things including<br>
CommandSchedule.getInstance().cancel(currentPathCommand)<br>
setting a timeout on the command (this timeout interrrupts it) but still not really the right solutions.<br>
Tried Other methods to interrupt / move the command into sub systems etc.</p>
<p>Any help, guidance or places to look for examples or best ways to do this so we can interrupt the drivetopose pathplanner command would be helpful!</p>
